WEBVTT

00:53.250 --> 00:55.250
[LILY CRYING]

02:09.792 --> 02:11.125
YOUR MOTHER...

02:11.125 --> 02:11.750
HOW IS SHE HOLDING UP?

02:11.750 --> 02:13.959
SHE CRIES A LOT.

02:13.959 --> 02:15.542
I UNDERSTAND.

02:15.542 --> 02:18.041
AND YOU?
HOW ARE YOU?

02:19.625 --> 02:20.667
PEOPLE ASK ME
THAT A LOT.

02:20.667 --> 02:21.750
IT'S A WEIRD
QUESTION.

02:21.750 --> 02:23.333
EVERY TIME
I START TO GIVE

02:23.333 --> 02:24.291
TOO LONG
OF AN ANSWER,

02:24.291 --> 02:25.333
WHICH I'M STARTING
TO DO RIGHT NOW,

02:25.333 --> 02:27.959
THOSE SAME PEOPLE
GET VERY
UNCOMFORTABLE.

02:30.500 --> 02:31.542
NOT YOU, THOUGH,
HUH?

02:31.542 --> 02:32.125
I GUESS YOU'RE
AN OLD PRO AT THIS.

02:32.125 --> 02:34.041
YOU COULD SAY THAT.

02:34.041 --> 02:36.333
I'M FINE.

02:42.458 --> 02:43.542
[CLEARS THROAT]
THAT ONE.

02:46.000 --> 02:47.375
VERY NICE CHOICE.

02:47.375 --> 02:50.000
VERY TASTEFUL.

02:51.000 --> 02:52.417
THANK YOU.

02:57.667 --> 02:59.333
Joey: HEY.

02:59.333 --> 03:00.208
HEY.

03:00.208 --> 03:03.000
WHAT'S WITH
THE FURROWED BROW?

03:03.000 --> 03:03.917
BETTER WATCH OUT.

03:03.917 --> 03:04.750
YOU'RE GONNA
GIVE YOURSELF A WRINKLE.

03:04.750 --> 03:05.875
PACEY, I'VE GOT
SOME BAD NEWS.

03:05.875 --> 03:08.667
AW, WHY DON'T
YOU LOOK LIKE
YOU'RE KIDDING?

03:08.667 --> 03:09.875
DOUG
GAVE ME A CALL.

03:09.875 --> 03:11.125
HE SAID HE'S BEEN
TRYING TO GET
IN TOUCH WITH YOU.

03:11.125 --> 03:13.000
HE LEFT YOU
A BUNCH OF MESSAGES
AT THE RESTAURANT.

03:13.000 --> 03:13.750
YEAH, I KNOW.
I MEANT TO CALL HIM BACK,

03:13.750 --> 03:14.959
BUT WHAT ARE YOU
GONNA DO?

03:14.959 --> 03:16.333
YOU PROBABLY
SHOULD'VE.

03:16.333 --> 03:17.625
WHAT'S GOING ON?

03:19.000 --> 03:21.500
IT'S MITCH.
UM...

03:22.959 --> 03:24.333
HE'S DEAD.

03:26.458 --> 03:28.083
WHAT?

03:33.041 --> 03:35.000
WELL, HOW?

03:35.000 --> 03:36.458
IT WAS
A CAR ACCIDENT.

03:38.625 --> 03:40.041
AND I-I-IS EVERYBODY--
I MEAN--

03:40.041 --> 03:41.458
THEY'RE ALL FINE.

03:41.458 --> 03:43.041
IT WAS JUST MITCH.
HE WAS ALONE.

03:43.041 --> 03:43.917
WHEN DID THIS
HAPPEN, JO?

03:43.917 --> 03:46.125
IT HAPPENED A COUPLE
OF NIGHTS AGO.

03:48.083 --> 03:49.333
OHH.

03:52.625 --> 03:54.417
HOW'S DAWSON DOING?

03:54.417 --> 03:56.417
WELL,
HE'S NOT SO GOOD.

03:56.417 --> 03:56.542
HIS FATHER'S DEAD.

03:58.417 --> 04:00.208
RIGHT.
THAT'S A STUPID QUESTION.

04:00.208 --> 04:02.208
NO, YOU'RE ENTITLED,
BELIEVE ME.

04:02.208 --> 04:04.083
I'VE SAID ABOUT
800 STUPID THINGS

04:04.083 --> 04:05.000
TO HIM IN THE LAST
COUPLE OF DAYS,

04:05.000 --> 04:06.458
BUT, UM, YOU WANT
TO COME WITH ME?

04:10.375 --> 04:11.917
DO YOU REALLY THINK
THAT I SHOULD?

04:11.917 --> 04:12.917
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

04:12.917 --> 04:14.959
WELL, I...

04:17.375 --> 04:19.666
MAYBE HE DOESN'T
WANT ME THERE, JO.

04:21.125 --> 04:22.917
OK, YOUR FATHER
DIES TOMORROW.

04:22.917 --> 04:24.083
YOU'RE
AT THE FUNERAL.

04:24.083 --> 04:25.000
YOU LOOK UP,
AND YOU SEE DAWSON.

04:25.000 --> 04:26.208
WOULD THAT MEAN
SOMETHING TO YOU?

04:26.208 --> 04:28.083
WOULD SEEING ONE
OF YOUR OLDEST
FRIENDS MEAN SOM--

04:28.083 --> 04:29.125
JUST GIVE ME
5 MINUTES.

04:29.125 --> 04:29.375
BE RIGHT THERE.

04:45.125 --> 04:46.834
CAN I TALK TO YOU
ABOUT SOMETHING?

04:46.834 --> 04:48.041
SURE.

04:49.333 --> 04:50.750
I'M NERVOUS.

04:50.750 --> 04:51.542
ABOUT WHAT?

04:52.041 --> 04:53.834
SEEING HIM.

04:53.834 --> 04:55.917
WHY?

04:55.917 --> 04:58.375
BECAUSE I DON'T
KNOW WHAT TO SAY.

04:58.375 --> 05:01.959
I DON'T THINK
HE'S EXPECTING YOU
TO GIVE A SPEECH, JEN.

05:01.959 --> 05:04.291
I COULDN'T SLEEP
LAST NIGHT.

05:04.291 --> 05:06.291
I WAS UP AND TOSSING
AND TURNING,

05:06.291 --> 05:07.708
TRYING TO FIGURE OUT
WHAT TO SAY,

05:07.708 --> 05:08.792
HOW I WAS
GONNA ACT.

05:08.792 --> 05:10.500
NO ONE EVER
KNOWS WHAT TO SAY,

05:10.500 --> 05:11.542
BUT WHEN TIM DIED,
YOU WOULDN'T BELIEVE

05:11.542 --> 05:13.792
SOME OF THE THINGS
THAT PEOPLE SAID TO ME.

05:13.792 --> 05:16.500
BUT THE THING IS,
NO MATTER WHAT YOU SAY
OR WHAT YOU DO,

05:16.500 --> 05:18.208
DAWSON IS ALONE
IN THIS, OK?

05:18.208 --> 05:21.166
THERE ISN'T
A WORD OR A SENTENCE
IN THE ENGLISH LANGUAGE

05:21.166 --> 05:23.834
THAT CAN TAKE AWAY
THE KIND OF PAIN
THAT HE'S DEALING WITH.

05:23.834 --> 05:25.959
WELL, SO THEN,
WHAT DO I DO?

05:26.875 --> 05:28.542
YOU'VE JUST
GOTTA FIGURE OUT

05:28.542 --> 05:31.333
YOUR OWN WAY
OF BEING THERE FOR HIM.

05:33.708 --> 05:36.000
OK.

05:42.583 --> 05:44.583
[LILY GURGLES]

06:12.083 --> 06:14.583
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

06:46.834 --> 06:49.041
[SIGHS]

06:56.834 --> 06:58.542
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

06:58.542 --> 07:00.458
YOU HAVING
A GOOD BIRTHDAY?

07:01.542 --> 07:02.750
YEAH, DEFINITELY.

07:02.750 --> 07:05.750
HOW'S IT FEEL
TO BE 12 YEARS OLD?

07:05.750 --> 07:06.708
PRETTY GOOD.

07:06.708 --> 07:09.125
I THINK I'M READY
FOR A GIRLFRIEND.

07:09.125 --> 07:10.667
OH, YOU THINK SO?

07:10.667 --> 07:11.708
YEAH.

07:11.708 --> 07:13.250
WELL, I'D SAY
GIVE IT A FEW YEARS.

07:13.250 --> 07:14.625
YOU'VE GOT
PLENTY OF TIME

07:14.625 --> 07:17.166
BEFORE GIRLS START
CLOUDING YOUR HEAD.

07:17.166 --> 07:19.333
HA, OK.

07:19.333 --> 07:20.750
DID YOU LIKE
ALL YOUR GIFTS?

07:20.750 --> 07:22.959
YEAH, I LOVED 'EM,
ESPECIALLY THE 1941  VIDEO.

07:22.959 --> 07:25.250
WHICH WAS NOT
EASY TO FIND,
LET ME TELL YOU.

07:25.250 --> 07:26.917
THANK YOU, DAD.
DON'T MENTION IT.

07:26.917 --> 07:28.166
YOU KNOW,
I COULD BE WRONG,

07:28.166 --> 07:30.917
BUT I THINK YOU'VE
GOT ONE MORE GIFT
COMING TO YOU.

07:30.917 --> 07:31.667
NOPE.
I OPENED THEM ALL.

07:31.667 --> 07:33.834
ARE YOU SURE?
PRETTY SURE.

07:33.834 --> 07:34.834
I DON'T KNOW...

07:34.834 --> 07:37.000
I THINK MAYBE YOU
BETTER TAKE A LOOK...

07:37.000 --> 07:38.834
IN THE CLOSET.

07:40.083 --> 07:41.291
GO ON.

07:48.166 --> 07:48.959
WELL, COME ON!
BRING IT OUT.

07:48.959 --> 07:50.959
OPEN IT UP.

07:57.291 --> 07:59.333
THE GUY AT THE STORE SAID
IT WAS A REAL GOOD ONE
FOR MAKING MOVIES.

07:59.333 --> 08:01.458
GREAT EDITING
CAPABILITIES,

08:01.458 --> 08:03.750
AND IT COMES
WITH ITS OWN TRIPOD.

08:05.333 --> 08:07.291
THANK YOU, DAD.
HA HA.

08:07.291 --> 08:10.917
YOU'RE WELCOME,
DAWSON.

08:10.917 --> 08:11.959
DAD, THIS...

08:13.583 --> 08:15.000
THIS MUST HAVE BEEN
REALLY EXPENSIVE,

08:15.000 --> 08:16.166
BUT YOU'RE NOT
GONNA REGRET IT.

08:16.166 --> 08:17.458
I SWEAR, I'M GONNA
MAKE SO MANY MOVIES
ON THIS.

08:17.458 --> 08:18.458
THIS IS NOT A PHASE.

08:18.458 --> 08:19.166
OH, DON'T WORRY
ABOUT THAT, DAWSON.

08:19.166 --> 08:22.000
JUST ENJOY IT.

08:22.000 --> 08:25.208
LET THE THINGS YOU LOVE
BE YOUR ESCAPE.

08:34.250 --> 08:35.792
[KNOCK ON DOOR]
DAWSON?

08:38.582 --> 08:39.917
JOEY...HEY.

08:41.958 --> 08:42.332
YOU'RE SMILING.

08:42.332 --> 08:45.166
I WAS?

08:45.166 --> 08:47.250
YOU WERE.

09:01.542 --> 09:04.375
IS THERE ANYTHING
I CAN DO?

09:04.375 --> 09:06.792
UM...YEAH, ACTUALLY.
YOU KNOW WHAT? THERE IS.

09:06.792 --> 09:08.291
WOULD YOU MIND
WATCHING LILY
FOR A LITTLE BIT?

09:08.291 --> 09:09.208
MY MOM FELL ASLEEP.
I'VE GOTTA GET TO
THE FUNERAL HOME.

09:09.208 --> 09:11.291
OF COURSE.

09:11.291 --> 09:12.500
GREAT.

09:14.041 --> 09:16.667
IS THAT WHAT YOU'RE
WEARING? IT'S NICE.

09:16.667 --> 09:19.750
UH, NO. ACTUALLY,
IT'S FOR MY DAD.

09:19.750 --> 09:21.375
HE'S GONNA
BE BURIED IN IT.

09:23.625 --> 09:25.583
I'M SORRY.

09:27.542 --> 09:29.458
JO, THAT'S OK.
YOU COULDN'T
HAVE KNOWN THAT.

09:32.125 --> 09:33.750
I WON'T BE LONG.

11:09.834 --> 11:11.667
WHY DON'T YOU LET ME TAKE HER
FOR A WHILE, DEAR?

11:11.667 --> 11:15.291
I'M AFRAID I CAN'T
DO THAT, GRAMS.

11:15.291 --> 11:16.792
LILY HERE OFFERS
A GREAT BUFFER.

11:16.792 --> 11:18.750
AS LONG AS
I HOLD HER,

11:18.750 --> 11:19.834
PEOPLE TEND NOT
TO COME UP TO ME

11:19.834 --> 11:22.000
AND OFFER
THEIR PLATITUDES.

11:25.917 --> 11:27.333
WHERE'S YOUR MOTHER?

11:27.333 --> 11:31.000
SHE'S UPSTAIRS.

11:31.000 --> 11:32.625
SHE WON'T COME DOWN.

11:37.500 --> 11:39.333
SO, WHAT'S YOURS?

11:39.333 --> 11:40.417
MY WHAT?

11:40.417 --> 11:42.875
YOUR PLATITUDE.

11:45.125 --> 11:48.500
I'M AFRAID I'M FRESH OUT.

11:48.500 --> 11:49.708
REALLY?

11:51.917 --> 11:53.625
I THOUGHT FOR SURE
YOU'D WHIP OUT

11:53.625 --> 11:56.041
"THE LORD WORKS
IN MYSTERIOUS WAYS."

11:56.041 --> 11:57.708
HMM.

11:57.708 --> 12:01.166
THE LORD AND I,
WE...

12:01.166 --> 12:03.750
WE AREN'T ON SPEAKING
TERMS THIS WEEK.

12:35.708 --> 12:37.708
[CLANK]

12:40.166 --> 12:41.875
LISTEN, JOEY...

12:41.875 --> 12:44.250
I DON'T WANT YOU
CLIMBING UP THE TRELLIS
ANYMORE, OK?

12:44.250 --> 12:46.417
IT'S DANGEROUS.
YOU COULD HURT YOURSELF,

12:46.417 --> 12:49.250
AND IF THAT HAPPENED,
I DON'T THINK MY SON
WOULD EVER FORGIVE ME.

12:49.250 --> 12:51.375
YEAH, RIGHT.

12:53.750 --> 12:54.959
SOONER OR LATER,
JOEY,

12:54.959 --> 12:57.041
HE'S GONNA PULL HIS HEAD
OUT OF THE SAND.

12:57.041 --> 12:59.500
HE'LL FIGURE IT OUT.

12:59.500 --> 13:02.708
PROBABLY NOT
AS SOON AS YOU'D LIKE,

13:02.708 --> 13:04.208
BOYS ARE STUPID
LIKE THAT.

13:31.458 --> 13:32.708
HEY.

13:33.291 --> 13:35.333
HEY.

13:36.208 --> 13:37.417
WHAT YOU DOING?

13:37.417 --> 13:38.667
TRYING TO DECIDE
BETWEEN A GLASS
OF ORANGE JUICE

13:38.667 --> 13:40.375
AND A BOTTLE
OF WINE.

13:40.375 --> 13:42.291
ANY THOUGHTS?

13:42.291 --> 13:45.458
WELL, WINE'S FINE,
BUT WHISKEY'S QUICKER.

13:45.458 --> 13:47.875
WHAT ABOUT NARCOTICS?

13:47.875 --> 13:48.875
OH, EVEN BETTER.

13:48.875 --> 13:50.125
YOU KNOW,
TIMES LIKE THIS,

13:50.125 --> 13:51.792
I REALLY WISH
I WAS MORE OF
A DRUG PERSON,

13:51.792 --> 13:52.792
BUT I DON'T KNOW.

13:52.792 --> 13:55.583
STARTING UP JUST SEEMS
LIKE SUCH A HASSLE.

13:55.583 --> 13:58.250
YEAH, PLUS,
YOU CAN'T REALLY SCORE
ANY GOOD DOPE IN CAPESIDE.

13:58.250 --> 14:00.166
GOOD POINT.
ORANGE JUICE IT IS.

14:03.959 --> 14:05.792
SO, I'VE BEEN TRYING
TO FIGURE EXACTLY

14:05.792 --> 14:07.750
WHAT IT IS THAT I'M
SUPPOSED TO SAY TO YOU.

14:09.166 --> 14:11.083
I FEEL TERRIBLE, DAWSON,
I REALLY DO.

14:13.542 --> 14:16.166
I MEAN, I CAN'T IMAGINE
WHAT YOU'RE GOING THROUGH,

14:16.166 --> 14:17.792
BUT I FEEL SO HELPLESS.

14:18.667 --> 14:20.291
I MEAN, IF THIS WERE
ABOUT A GIRL,

14:20.291 --> 14:21.458
I COULD OFFER
SAGE ADVICE,

14:21.458 --> 14:25.083
BUT...THIS IS OUT
OF MY LEAGUE.

14:26.917 --> 14:30.000
THE ONLY PERSON THAT
WAS EVER TAKEN FROM ME
WAS MY GRANDFATHER,

14:30.000 --> 14:33.166
AND THAT WAS A LONG TIME
COMING, YOU KNOW.

14:33.166 --> 14:34.834
SO HERE'S
WHAT I'M GONNA DO.

14:34.834 --> 14:36.083
I'M GONNA GIVE YOU
A HUG,

14:36.083 --> 14:39.000
AND I'M NOT GONNA LET GO
FOR A REALLY LONG TIME.

14:39.000 --> 14:40.708
I'M GONNA TELL YOU
THAT I LOVE YOU,

14:40.708 --> 14:42.625
WHICH IS ACTUALLY
A PRETTY GOOD DEAL,

14:42.625 --> 14:43.875
'CAUSE THAT MEANS
THAT I'LL DO ANYTHING

14:43.875 --> 14:46.166
ON THE OFF CHANCE
IT'LL MAKE YOU
A LITTLE LESS SAD.

14:48.875 --> 14:50.208
THAT SOUNDS
VERY GOOD TO ME.

15:01.125 --> 15:03.000
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

15:06.917 --> 15:10.667
I, UH, CAN'T BELIEVE
THAT HE'S GONE.

15:10.667 --> 15:13.875
I KEEP EXPECTING
TO HEAR HIS CAR
IN THE DRIVEWAY,

15:13.875 --> 15:15.291
HIS KEYS
IN THE LOCK,

15:15.291 --> 15:16.750
FOOTSTEPS
ON THE STAIRS.

15:19.750 --> 15:22.917
SO, HOW'S
THE PARTY?

15:22.917 --> 15:26.083
IT'S FABULOUS.
THE PATÃ‰ IS ALL THE RAGE.

15:26.083 --> 15:28.708
AND HOW'S OUR BOY?

15:28.708 --> 15:30.667
GREAT. HE'S KEEPING IT
ALL TOGETHER.

15:30.667 --> 15:32.458
WHICH IS EXACTLY
WHAT BOTHERS ME.

15:32.458 --> 15:34.083
ME, TOO.

15:34.083 --> 15:35.542
HE'S STUBBORN, JOEY.
HE'S JUST LIKE
HIS FATHER.

15:38.208 --> 15:41.041
YOU KNOW,
I KNOW THIS PROBABLY
DOESN'T MEAN MUCH NOW,

15:41.041 --> 15:43.792
BUT HE'S NOT REALLY GONE,
YOU KNOW.

15:43.792 --> 15:45.583
'CAUSE IF EVER
THERE WAS SOMEONE

15:45.583 --> 15:48.041
WHO WAS AN ABSOLUTE
REFLECTION OF HIS FATHER,

15:48.041 --> 15:49.041
IT'S DAWSON.

15:49.041 --> 15:50.125
YOU THINK SO?

15:53.625 --> 15:55.333
YOU KNOW, GROWING UP,

15:55.333 --> 15:58.208
SPENDING THAT TIME
WITH YOU GUYS...

15:58.208 --> 16:01.792
I THINK I WAS TOO LITTLE
TO REALLY UNDERSTAND IT,

16:01.792 --> 16:04.125
BUT I--I ALWAYS KNEW
THERE WAS SOMETHING SPECIAL

16:04.125 --> 16:06.083
ABOUT THE WAY YOU GUYS
LOOKED AT EACH OTHER.

16:06.083 --> 16:10.792
LIKE YOU WERE IN
ON THIS GREAT LITTLE SECRET

16:10.792 --> 16:12.458
THAT THE REST OF US
WEREN'T PRIVY TO,

16:12.458 --> 16:16.000
AND MY PARENTS
NEVER HAD THAT...

16:16.000 --> 16:19.792
NOT EVEN
IN THE BEST OF TIMES.

16:19.792 --> 16:22.083
I'M NOT GONNA SIT HERE
AND--AND TRY TO PRETEND

16:22.083 --> 16:26.000
TO KNOW WHAT WAS GOING
THROUGH HIS MIND
BEFORE HE DIED, BUT...

16:26.000 --> 16:28.291
I KNOW YOUR HUSBAND
LOVED YOU VERY MUCH.

16:42.166 --> 16:43.125
HEY.

16:45.083 --> 16:47.959
DAWSON.

16:47.959 --> 16:49.500
HEY, MAN.

16:49.500 --> 16:52.291
THANKS FOR COMIN'.

16:52.291 --> 16:54.875
OF COURSE...

16:54.875 --> 16:56.166
BUT I CAN'T SAY
THAT THIS IS EXACTLY

16:56.166 --> 16:58.291
THE WAY I WANTED
TO SEE YOU AGAIN
FOR THE FIRST TIME.

16:58.291 --> 17:00.750
YEAH, I KNOW
WHAT YOU MEAN.

17:00.750 --> 17:02.667
HOW WAS YOUR SUMMER?

17:02.667 --> 17:06.000
MY SUMMER
WAS REALLY GOOD.

17:06.000 --> 17:07.583
IT WAS REALLY,
REALLY GOOD, ACTUALLY.

17:07.583 --> 17:09.125
IT TOTALLY
CLEARED MY HEAD.

17:09.125 --> 17:11.333
GOOD.

17:11.333 --> 17:12.416
HOW'S FILM SCHOOL
TREATIN' YA?

17:12.416 --> 17:15.000
UH...

17:15.000 --> 17:15.541
I'M GONNA BE DROPPIN'
OUT, ACTUALLY.

17:15.541 --> 17:18.791
WHY?

17:18.791 --> 17:22.040
[SIGHS]
IT'S A LONG STORY.

17:23.875 --> 17:25.333
GOTCHA.

17:30.583 --> 17:31.708
I'M SORRY, DAWSON.

17:33.959 --> 17:36.375
I WISH I HAD SOMETHIN' BETTER
TO SAY TO YOU THAN THAT,

17:36.375 --> 17:37.041
BUT THAT'S REALLY
WHAT IT BOILS DOWN TO.

17:37.041 --> 17:39.583
I'M REALLY, REALLY SORRY.

17:45.625 --> 17:47.500
REMEMBER THE TIME
HE CAUGHT US
SMOKING DOWN HERE?

17:49.750 --> 17:52.291
YEAH. I, UH...
OF COURSE I REMEMBER.

17:52.291 --> 17:55.083
SIXTH GRADE, RIGHT?
I DON'T THINK I'VE EVER
SEEN YOUR FATHER SO MAD.

17:55.083 --> 17:56.417
BEING MITCH,
HE HAD TO TELL US

17:56.417 --> 17:57.542
THAT HE WAS JUST
CONCERNED FOR US,

17:57.542 --> 17:58.333
WHICH WAS A BIT
OF A SURPRISE TO ME

17:58.333 --> 17:59.875
BECAUSE IF IT WAS
MY FATHER,

17:59.875 --> 18:01.166
IT WOULD BE KIND
OF A DIFFERENT STORY.

18:01.166 --> 18:02.708
IN FACT, I GUARANTEE
I'D STILL BE SMOKING
TO THIS DAY

18:02.708 --> 18:03.542
JUST TO PISS HIM OFF.

18:07.000 --> 18:08.208
AHH...

18:11.041 --> 18:12.208
WELL...

18:14.125 --> 18:15.417
I SHOULD PROBABLY
HEAD INSIDE

18:15.417 --> 18:16.750
AND MAKE MYSELF USEFUL
OR SOMETHING.

18:16.750 --> 18:18.250
ALL RIGHT?
OF COURSE.

18:18.250 --> 18:20.125
[SIGHS] IT WAS GOOD
TO SEE YOU, PACE.

18:20.959 --> 18:23.083
YEAH.

18:23.083 --> 18:23.333
COME HERE.

18:32.542 --> 18:35.875
[SIGHS]

18:47.125 --> 18:47.417
DAWSON.

18:49.792 --> 18:51.375
YOU PROBABLY DON'T
REMEMBER ME, DAWSON,

18:51.375 --> 18:52.959
BUT I'M SUSAN.
I'M AN OLD FRIEND

18:52.959 --> 18:54.667
OF YOUR MOTHER'S
FROM COLLEGE.

18:54.667 --> 18:56.792
RIGHT. YOU'RE MY MOM'S
DEADHEAD FRIEND.

18:56.792 --> 18:58.458
[LAUGHS]
THAT'S RIGHT.

18:58.458 --> 19:01.166
UH, TELL ME,
ARE YOU DEALING
WITH YOUR GRIEF?

19:01.166 --> 19:04.291
UH...
I'M DEALING.

19:04.291 --> 19:04.917
HOW ARE YOU
DEALING WITH IT?

19:04.917 --> 19:09.083
UM, NOT TO BE RUDE,

19:09.083 --> 19:10.625
BUT I--I DON'T KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT.

19:10.625 --> 19:13.208
WHERE ARE YOU CHANNELING
ALL THE FEELINGS
YOU'RE HAVING

19:13.208 --> 19:16.458
ABOUT YOUR FATHER'S
PASSING?

19:16.458 --> 19:18.250
UM...

19:18.250 --> 19:19.792
YOU KNOW,
NOT TO BE RUDE AGAIN,

19:19.792 --> 19:21.792
BUT I REALLY DON'T HAVE
THE TIME OR THE LUXURY.

19:21.792 --> 19:22.750
[TELEPHONE RINGS]
OH, YOU MUST TAKE
THE TIME, DAWSON.

19:22.750 --> 19:23.917
Mitch: HI.

19:23.917 --> 19:25.291
YOU'VE REACHED
THE LEERYS...

19:25.291 --> 19:26.834
MINUS DAWSON, THAT IS,

19:26.834 --> 19:30.250
WHO CAN BE REACHED
IN SUNNY CALIFORNIA
THESE DAYS.

19:30.250 --> 19:33.000
IF YOU HAVE A MESSAGE
FOR GALE, LILY,
OR MYSELF, HOWEVER,

19:33.000 --> 19:34.375
YOU CAN LEAVE IT AT--

19:38.458 --> 19:39.834
HEY.
I'M FINE.

19:39.834 --> 19:42.417
I'M...

19:43.834 --> 19:45.083
I'M FINE.

20:03.542 --> 20:04.542
[CLEARS THROAT]

20:10.333 --> 20:12.375
NOT ONE OF MY FINER
MOMENTS, HUH?

20:16.250 --> 20:18.792
YOU KNOW,
A LONG TIME AGO--

20:18.792 --> 20:20.583
IT MUST HAVE BEEN
A COUPLE OF MONTHS
AFTER MY MOM PASSED AWAY--

20:20.583 --> 20:24.583
I WAS DIGGING THROUGH
THIS DRAWER IN THE KITCHEN

20:24.583 --> 20:26.625
LOOKING FOR A PEN
OR SOMETHING,

20:26.625 --> 20:31.375
AND I CAME ACROSS
THIS GROCERY LIST
SHE HAD MADE,

20:31.375 --> 20:35.417
AND IT WAS FILLED
WITH ALL THESE LITTLE
HEART-SHAPED DOODLES,

20:35.417 --> 20:37.291
AND I JUST...LOST IT.

20:37.291 --> 20:40.625
I CRIED LIKE A BABY
FOR HOURS.

20:42.375 --> 20:45.708
IF WHAT JUST HAPPENED
TO YOU IN THERE

20:45.708 --> 20:47.125
HAD HAPPENED TO ME
BACK THEN,

20:47.125 --> 20:48.834
I WOULD HAVE
RUN AWAY SCREAMING.

20:48.834 --> 20:51.375
I CAN'T DO THAT.

20:51.375 --> 20:52.500
WHO SAYS?

20:52.500 --> 20:54.792
I DO. I CAN'T.

20:54.792 --> 20:57.083
MY MOM'S A WRECK.
I GOTTA KEEP IT
TOGETHER.

20:57.083 --> 20:59.542
SHE'S ALLOWED
TO BE A WRECK,
AND SO ARE YOU.

21:03.083 --> 21:05.959
I'LL MAKE YOU A DEAL.

21:05.959 --> 21:07.291
YOU TAKE CARE OF YOUR MOM,

21:07.291 --> 21:09.125
I'LL TAKE CARE OF YOU.

21:14.375 --> 21:17.625
I GOTTA SAY, JO, I--

21:17.625 --> 21:19.375
WHEN YOUR MOM DIED,
I SYMPATHIZED WITH YOU,
AND I REALLY FELT BAD,

21:19.375 --> 21:21.834
BUT I HAD NO IDEA
IT FELT LIKE THIS.

21:21.834 --> 21:23.750
NOTHING FEELS REAL.
IT'S LIKE I'VE BEEN

21:23.750 --> 21:25.333
TRANSPORTED TO SOME
ALTERNATE UNIVERSE

21:25.333 --> 21:26.792
WHERE I'M JUST
WALKING AROUND

21:26.792 --> 21:27.542
OUTSIDE MY BODY
ALL DAY LONG.

21:32.250 --> 21:34.792
IT'LL GET BETTER.
I PROMISE.

21:34.792 --> 21:37.500
THAT'S GOOD.
ANY, UH, ADVICE

21:37.500 --> 21:38.750
ON HOW I SHOULD
DEAL WITH THE FACT

21:38.750 --> 21:40.291
THAT MY FATHER'S
DEATH WAS ALMOST
ENTIRELY MY FAULT?

21:40.291 --> 21:44.625
WHAT? HOW DO YOU
FIGURE THAT?

21:44.625 --> 21:46.291
COME ON, JO.
THINK ABOUT IT.

21:46.291 --> 21:47.708
IF I HADN'T COME BACK
AND LAID ALL THIS
ON HIM,

21:47.708 --> 21:48.959
NONE OF THIS
WOULD'VE HAPPENED.

21:48.959 --> 21:50.500
DAWSON, LOOK AT ME.

21:50.500 --> 21:54.000
YOU FATHER DIED
IN A CAR ACCIDENT.

21:54.000 --> 21:55.291
THERE WAS NOTHING
YOU COULD DO TO STOP THAT.

21:55.291 --> 21:57.583
THAT'S NOT ENTIRELY
TRUE, JO.

21:57.583 --> 21:59.917
THAT'S, I MEAN...

21:59.917 --> 22:02.458
FIRST OFF, IF I HADN'T
SHOWED UP THAT MORNING,

22:02.458 --> 22:03.834
MY MOM WOULDN'T HAVE
MADE ME BREAKFAST,

22:03.834 --> 22:05.792
WHICH MEANS THEY WOULDN'T
HAVE RUN OUT OF MILK,

22:05.792 --> 22:08.166
WHICH MEANS MY DAD
WOULDN'T HAVE HAD TO DRIVE
TO THE STORE THAT NIGHT

22:08.166 --> 22:09.375
SO LILY WOULD HAVE
SOME IN THE MORNING.

22:09.375 --> 22:10.333
THAT'S CRAZY.

22:10.333 --> 22:12.458
DON'T TELL ME
WHAT'S CRAZY, JO.

22:12.458 --> 22:14.834
FOR ALL I KNOW,
MY DAD WAS DRIVING
ALONG THAT NIGHT,

22:14.834 --> 22:17.834
PISSED, HAVING
SOME ARGUMENT
WITH ME IN HIS HEAD

22:17.834 --> 22:18.500
WHICH CAUSED HIM
TO TAKE HIS EYES
OFF THE ROAD

22:18.500 --> 22:20.125
JUST LONG ENOUGH
TO--

22:20.125 --> 22:21.583
LOOK, YOU CAN'T
DO THIS TO YOURSELF.

22:21.583 --> 22:22.959
[SIGHS]

22:22.959 --> 22:24.208
YOU--YOU KNOW
WHAT HE SAID TO ME

22:24.208 --> 22:25.458
THE LAST TIME
I SAW HIM?

22:25.458 --> 22:28.000
Joey: HMM?

22:28.000 --> 22:30.083
HE SAID THAT I WAS
MAKING A HUGE MISTAKE

22:30.083 --> 22:31.458
AND THAT HE WAS
DISAPPOINTED IN ME.

22:37.500 --> 22:39.208
I KNOW. YOU TOLD ME THAT.

22:39.208 --> 22:43.667
YOU REMEMBER WHAT ELSE
YOU TOLD ME?

22:43.667 --> 22:46.625
HE SAID HE LOVED YOU
VERY MUCH.

22:51.917 --> 22:53.000
I'LL NEVER
GO THROUGH LIFE

22:53.000 --> 22:58.083
DOUBTING THAT MY FATHER
LOVED ME, JO, BUT...

22:58.083 --> 23:01.917
DO YOU HAVE ANY IDEA
HOW MUCH IT SUCKS

23:01.917 --> 23:04.625
TO KNOW THAT MY FATHER
WAS DISAPPOINTED IN ME
THE DAY HE DIED?

23:07.208 --> 23:10.291
AND HE WAS RIGHT.
I WAS ACTING CRAZY
LIKE A SPOILED BRAT,

23:10.291 --> 23:12.375
AND IF
I'D LISTENED TO HIM,

23:12.375 --> 23:13.375
HE WOULD'VE BEEN
DRIVING ME
TO THE AIRPORT

23:13.375 --> 23:15.083
INSTEAD OF DRIVING
TO HIS DEATH.

23:35.083 --> 23:36.959
YOU ALL RIGHT,
DEAR?

23:36.959 --> 23:39.875
OH, I'M HANGING
IN THERE, I GUESS.

23:42.291 --> 23:44.083
YOU KNOW, EVERY NIGHT
FOR 46 YEARS,

23:44.083 --> 23:46.375
I PRAYED THE GOOD LORD
WOULD TAKE ME FIRST.

23:46.375 --> 23:48.583
I NEVER WANTED
TO GO ON WITHOUT HIM.

23:48.583 --> 23:51.041
I DIDN'T THINK
I WAS CAPABLE OF IT.

23:51.041 --> 23:53.834
BUT SOMEHOW, I WAS.

23:53.834 --> 23:57.583
IT WASN'T EASY,
BUT INEVITABLY
THERE COMES A DAY

23:57.583 --> 24:00.542
THAT ISN'T AS BAD
AS THE ONE BEFORE IT.

24:00.542 --> 24:01.750
AND UNTIL THEN?

24:01.750 --> 24:05.333
WELL, THAT'S
WHAT PRESCRIPTION
MEDICATION IS FOR.

24:05.333 --> 24:07.625
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

24:08.959 --> 24:11.083
OH, IT'S A STRANGE
THING WE DO.

24:11.083 --> 24:13.625
WHAT'S THAT?

24:13.625 --> 24:16.417
FALLING IN LOVE.

24:16.417 --> 24:18.708
YOU SHARE YOUR LIFE
WITH ANOTHER PERSON.

24:18.708 --> 24:21.000
YOU--YOU GIVE THEM
YOUR HEART

24:21.000 --> 24:24.333
TO THE EXTENT
THAT LOSING THEM COULD
POTENTIALLY DESTROY YOU.

24:24.333 --> 24:28.917
IT'S A CRAZY THING
TO DO.

24:28.917 --> 24:32.250
YOU'RE RIGHT.
IT'S INSANE.

24:32.250 --> 24:35.500
THEN WHY ON EARTH
DO WE DO IT?

24:37.458 --> 24:39.083
WHAT ELSE IS THERE?

24:45.583 --> 24:49.125
OH, I WISH I STILL
LIVED NEXT DOOR.

24:49.125 --> 24:50.792
SO DO I.

24:50.792 --> 24:53.708
I COULD STAY
FOR A WHILE IF YOU LIKE,

24:53.708 --> 24:55.208
HELP OUT WITH LILY.

24:55.208 --> 24:57.875
OH, THAT IS SUCH
A GENEROUS OFFER,
EVELYN,

24:57.875 --> 24:59.959
AND I DO
LOVE YOU FOR IT,

24:59.959 --> 25:01.750
BUT, UM...
[SNIFFLES]

25:01.750 --> 25:03.542
NO, I--I THINK
DAWSON AND I

25:03.542 --> 25:06.000
ARE GONNA HAVE
TO MEET THIS ONE
HEAD ON.

25:06.000 --> 25:08.375
YOU SURE?

25:08.375 --> 25:10.750
[SIGHS]
I'M SURE.

25:10.750 --> 25:14.500
WELL, I UNDERSTAND,

25:14.500 --> 25:17.667
BUT DON'T YOU HESITATE
TO PICK UP THE PHONE,
YOUNG LADY.

25:17.667 --> 25:20.166
WE MERRY WIDOWS
HAVE TO STICK TOGETHER.

25:20.166 --> 25:22.375
[LAUGHS FAINTLY]

26:03.208 --> 26:04.041
HEY.

26:04.041 --> 26:06.708
HEY.

26:06.708 --> 26:08.458
EVERYONE'S
STARTING TO LEAVE.

26:12.000 --> 26:12.875
I'LL SEE YA.

26:12.875 --> 26:14.417
I CAN STAY
AS LONG AS YOU WANT.

26:14.417 --> 26:17.083
THAT'S SWEET
OF YOU, JO.

26:17.083 --> 26:18.250
I'M SERIOUS.

26:18.250 --> 26:19.417
I KNOW YOU ARE,

26:19.417 --> 26:20.417
BUT YOU GOTTA
GET BACK TO SCHOOL.

26:20.417 --> 26:21.375
SCHOOL DOESN'T MATTER
RIGHT NOW, DAWSON.

26:21.375 --> 26:22.458
I'LL BE OK.
DAWSON.

26:22.458 --> 26:24.792
JOEY,
I WANNA BE ALONE.

26:27.750 --> 26:29.166
OK?

26:32.083 --> 26:34.208
OK. CALL ME
IF YOU NEED ME.

26:34.208 --> 26:35.333
WILL YOU DO THAT?
I WILL.

26:39.583 --> 26:40.708
BYE.

26:55.959 --> 26:59.291
YOU KNOW, I CAN'T SAY
AS I HAVE EVER SEEN
THE POTTER B&B

26:59.291 --> 27:01.417
QUITE SO CROWDED.

27:04.375 --> 27:06.834
NOTHIN' LIKE A FUNERAL
TO DRUM UP BUSINESS.

27:06.834 --> 27:08.125
[SIGHS]

27:08.125 --> 27:11.500
YOU WANNA KNOW WHAT
THE WORST PART
ABOUT DEATH IS?

27:11.500 --> 27:14.417
IT HAS THIS
HORRIBLE TENDENCY

27:14.417 --> 27:16.625
OF PUTTING EVERYONE
IN A REALLY BAD MOOD.

27:16.625 --> 27:19.458
WHEN I GO,
I WANT TO GO IN A WAY

27:19.458 --> 27:21.375
IN WHICH IT MAKES
EVERYBODY LAUGH.

27:21.375 --> 27:22.667
YOU KNOW, LIKE,
NO MATTER HOW SUDDEN

27:22.667 --> 27:24.250
OR TRAGIC
THE CIRCUMSTANCES,

27:24.250 --> 27:25.959
YOU JUST CAN'T HELP
BUT LAUGH...

27:25.959 --> 27:28.583
LIKE GETTING RUN OVER
BY A CAR FULL OF CLOWNS.

27:28.583 --> 27:28.792
THAT'S KINDA FUNNY,
RIGHT?

27:31.166 --> 27:32.959
YOU SMILED.
MISSION ACCOMPLISHED.

27:36.625 --> 27:39.291
HE BLAMES HIMSELF,
YOU KNOW.

27:39.291 --> 27:41.000
WHY?

27:43.792 --> 27:46.250
WELL...

27:46.250 --> 27:48.667
HE WANTED
TO DROP OUT OF USC
AND MOVE TO BOSTON,

27:48.667 --> 27:49.875
AND MITCH THOUGHT
HE WAS CRAZY,

27:49.875 --> 27:51.500
AND THEY HAD
THIS HUGE BLOWOUT.

27:51.500 --> 27:54.417
WHY ON EARTH
WOULD DAWSON LEERY,
OF ALL PEOPLE,

27:54.417 --> 27:55.917
WANT TO DROP OUT
OF FILM SCHOOL?

28:01.917 --> 28:04.083
OH. HEH.

28:05.375 --> 28:06.667
I GET IT.

28:06.667 --> 28:10.083
IT'S OK.
YOU CAN TELL ME, JO.

28:10.083 --> 28:11.041
I'M NOT GONNA
GET UPSET.

28:11.041 --> 28:13.667
OH, PACE,
I DIDN'T ASK HIM TO,

28:13.667 --> 28:14.667
IF THAT'S WHAT
YOU MEAN. I--

28:14.667 --> 28:16.250
OH, LOOK.
IF ANYBODY UNDERSTANDS

28:16.250 --> 28:18.333
THE VARIOUS SHADES
OF GRAY HERE, IT'S ME,

28:18.333 --> 28:21.291
AND I THINK IT'S TIME
THE TWO OF YOU GOT YOUR SHOT...

28:23.333 --> 28:25.000
BECAUSE THE WAY I SEE IT,
YOU NEVER DID,

28:25.000 --> 28:27.834
AND THIS WORLD COULD USE
AS MANY ROMEO AND JULIETS
AS IT CAN GET.

28:27.834 --> 28:29.750
LOOK WHAT
HAPPENED TO THEM.

28:35.875 --> 28:37.125
[MITCH GRUNTS]

28:37.125 --> 28:40.458
THIS THING'S GONNA
BE TIP-TOP, BABY.
DON'T YOU WORRY.

28:40.458 --> 28:42.750
OH, I'M NOT WORRIED.

28:42.750 --> 28:45.583
I'LL JUST CALL
SOMEONE TO FIX IT
WHEN THE BOTTOM FALLS OUT.

28:45.583 --> 28:47.708
[LAUGHS]
OH, YE OF LITTLE FAITH.

28:47.708 --> 28:50.166
MRS. LEERY, HAVE I EVER
LET YOU DOWN?

28:50.166 --> 28:52.959
NO, MR. LEERY, YOU HAVEN'T.

28:58.208 --> 28:59.750
WHAT DO YOU THINK
HE'S GONNA BE?

28:59.750 --> 29:02.583
IF HE'S ANYTHING LIKE YOU,
A PAIN IN THE ASS.

29:04.750 --> 29:07.792
A LOT OF FATHERS
WANT THEIR SONS
TO PLAY BASEBALL.

29:07.792 --> 29:08.875
NOT ME.

29:08.875 --> 29:10.834
TEAM SPORTS
TEACH CONFORMITY.

29:12.875 --> 29:14.250
I HOPE HE'S A FREAK.

29:14.250 --> 29:15.959
A FREAK?
YEAH.

29:15.959 --> 29:18.458
FREAKS NEVER PEAK
IN HIGH SCHOOL.

29:18.458 --> 29:20.208
THEY NEVER GROW UP
TO SELL REAL ESTATE,

29:20.208 --> 29:22.542
DRINK HEAVILY
ON THE WEEKENDS,
AND BEAT THEIR KIDS.

29:22.542 --> 29:25.792
WELL, THEN,
LET'S HOPE FOR A FREAK.

29:31.375 --> 29:33.875
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

29:33.875 --> 29:35.000
MOM, YOU OK?

29:42.166 --> 29:43.291
UH...

29:43.291 --> 29:45.750
YEAH.

29:47.500 --> 29:49.166
FOR THE MOMENT.

29:53.083 --> 29:54.875
YOU WANNA KNOW WHAT
THE WORST PART IS?

29:54.875 --> 29:57.583
WHAT?

29:57.583 --> 30:01.125
SHE'LL NEVER EVEN KNOW
HE EXISTED.

30:01.125 --> 30:05.041
NOT IF I HAVE ANYTHING
TO DO ABOUT IT.

30:07.291 --> 30:11.333
SHE'S GONNA HEAR
ABOUT HER DADDY
EVERY CHANCE I GET.

30:15.291 --> 30:17.625
OH, I'M SUCH A MESS.

30:17.625 --> 30:18.583
I'M SORRY, HONEY.

30:18.583 --> 30:21.125
MOM, DON'T EVER APOLOGIZE.

30:21.125 --> 30:24.625
YOU ARE GONNA GET
YOUR LIFE BACK,
I PROMISE.

30:24.625 --> 30:27.875
MOM, I'M NOT GOING
ANYWHERE.

30:27.875 --> 30:30.500
NOT ANYTIME SOON.

30:32.166 --> 30:35.667
MY PLACE IS HERE
WITH YOU AND LILY.

30:35.667 --> 30:42.250
HONEY, YOU DON'T
HAVE TO BE SO STRONG
ALL THE TIME.

30:42.250 --> 30:44.708
YOU CAN FALL TO PIECES
JUST ABOUT ANY TIME
YOU WANT.

30:44.708 --> 30:46.458
THERE'S NOTHING
TO BE ASHAMED OF.

30:46.458 --> 30:49.500
I'M NOT ASHAMED.

30:49.500 --> 30:52.625
THERE'S--

30:54.542 --> 30:56.583
EVERYBODY KEEPS ON ASKING ME,
"HOW YOU DOIN'?

30:56.583 --> 31:00.917
HOW YOU FEELIN'?"

31:00.917 --> 31:04.834
TRUTH IS,
I DON'T FEEL ANYTHING.

31:06.542 --> 31:08.291
NOT A THING. I'M NUMB.

31:11.333 --> 31:15.917
WHICH, TO TELL YOU THE TRUTH,
IS REALLY NOT SO BAD.

31:15.917 --> 31:19.667
UM, THAT'S GREAT...

31:19.667 --> 31:23.792
UNTIL IT ALL
COMES CRUMBLING DOWN.

31:25.708 --> 31:31.291
WELL...UNTIL THEN.

31:55.917 --> 31:58.041
Mitch: OK, PACEY, NOW...

31:58.041 --> 31:59.667
GOT YOUR FOOT ON THE BRAKE?

31:59.667 --> 32:02.834
OK, PUT HER IN REVERSE...

32:02.834 --> 32:06.750
AND GENTLY--
OHH, OOH. CAREFUL.

32:06.750 --> 32:08.750
WATCH THE FLOWERS.
HEH HEH.

32:08.750 --> 32:11.208
MY WIFE
WILL HAVE ME KILLED.

32:11.208 --> 32:13.083
AND PARK.

32:13.083 --> 32:15.667
THERE YOU GO, PACEY.
YOU DID IT.

32:15.667 --> 32:17.208
YOU KNOW HOW TO DRIVE.

32:17.208 --> 32:18.083
NOT TERRIBLY WELL,
MIND YOU,

32:18.083 --> 32:20.875
BUT GOOD ENOUGH
TO PASS THAT TEST.

32:23.375 --> 32:25.000
THANK YOU FOR YOUR HELP,
MR. LEERY.

32:25.000 --> 32:26.166
IT'S MY PLEASURE.

32:26.166 --> 32:28.041
JUST SORRY YOUR FATHER
HAD TO WORK.

32:28.041 --> 32:29.750
[QUIETLY]
YEAH, ME, TOO.

32:29.750 --> 32:33.959
GO EASY ON HIM, PACEY.

32:33.959 --> 32:37.750
CAN'T ALWAYS BE FUN BEING
SHERIFF OF THESE PARTS.

32:37.750 --> 32:39.208
I GUESS I JUST WISH
HE WAS AROUND MORE.

32:41.875 --> 32:45.708
LISTEN, YOU EVER
WANNA PRACTICE,

32:45.708 --> 32:47.708
YOU KNOCK ON MY DOOR.

32:47.708 --> 32:49.458
OK?

32:49.458 --> 32:52.792
OK.

33:24.792 --> 33:28.208
[DOORBELL RINGS]

33:29.667 --> 33:33.000
HEY, MAN.

33:33.000 --> 33:34.625
HOW YA DOING TODAY?

33:34.625 --> 33:37.667
HE'S STILL DEAD.
IT STILL SUCKS.

33:37.667 --> 33:40.375
WANNA GO FOR A RIDE
WITH ME?

33:50.417 --> 33:52.333
WHAT THE HELL
ARE WE DOING HERE?

33:52.333 --> 33:53.834
WANNA SHOW YOU
SOMETHING.

33:57.834 --> 34:01.333
ACCORDING TO MY BROTHER,
YOUR FATHER WAS DRIVING
DOWN THE ROAD HERE

34:01.333 --> 34:03.000
AT ABOUT 45 MILES AN HOUR.

34:03.000 --> 34:04.417
WHICH IS, GRANTED,
A LITTLE BIT ABOVE
THE SPEED LIMIT,

34:04.417 --> 34:07.667
BUT NOT AT ALL UNUSUAL
FOR THIS STRETCH OF ROAD.

34:07.667 --> 34:11.458
AT THE SAME TIME,
A MAN NAMED GARY PETERS
WAS GETTING OFF WORK,

34:11.458 --> 34:14.291
DRIVING DOWN THE ROAD
A LITTLE FARTHER UP,
JUST AROUND THE BEND.

34:14.291 --> 34:15.208
GARY PETERS IS
A PRETTY AVERAGE GUY.

34:15.208 --> 34:18.833
35 YEARS OLD,
WIFE, 2 KIDS.

34:18.833 --> 34:20.291
WORKS AS
A BAGGAGE HANDLER
FOR BLUE STAR AIRLINES.

34:20.291 --> 34:23.208
AND GARY HAD TO PULL
A DOUBLE SHIFT THAT DAY,

34:23.208 --> 34:24.542
AND IT MUST'VE BEEN
A REAL BITCH

34:24.542 --> 34:25.708
'CAUSE WHEN HE CAME
AROUND THAT BEND,

34:25.708 --> 34:27.000
HE WAS ASLEEP
AT THE WHEEL.

34:27.000 --> 34:27.958
WHY ARE YOU DOING
THIS, PACEY?
WHY?

34:27.958 --> 34:30.583
BECAUSE
I WANT YOU TO KNOW

34:30.583 --> 34:32.250
THAT IT WAS A MAN
NAMED GARY PETERS
WHO KILLED YOUR FATHER.

34:32.250 --> 34:33.375
A GUY WHO SHOULD'VE
KNOWN BETTER

34:33.375 --> 34:35.500
THAN TO GET BEHIND
THE WHEEL OF A CAR.

34:35.500 --> 34:37.250
A GUY WHO,
FOR THE REST
OF HIS LIFE,

34:37.250 --> 34:39.041
WILL CARRY AROUND
THE GUILT OF TAKING
MITCH LEERY

34:39.041 --> 34:40.375
AWAY FROM HIS WIFE
AND 2 KIDS.

34:40.375 --> 34:44.250
AND I WANT YOU
TO KNOW THAT
THAT GUY IS NOT YOU.

34:44.250 --> 34:46.291
IT'S NOT YOU, DAWSON.

34:46.291 --> 34:48.708
DO NOT BLAME YOURSELF
FOR THIS.

34:48.708 --> 34:51.083
YOU WANNA GRIEVE?
YOU GO RIGHT AHEAD.
BE MY GUEST.

34:51.083 --> 34:52.917
BUT DO NOT
FOR ONE SINGLE SECOND

34:52.917 --> 34:53.958
THINK THAT THIS
IS YOUR FAULT,

34:53.958 --> 34:58.083
BECAUSE IT IS NOT
YOUR FAULT.

35:00.667 --> 35:02.166
YOU GOT YOUR FATHER
FOR 18 YEARS...

35:02.166 --> 35:05.125
AND THAT IS
A HELL OF A LOT MORE
THAN SOME PEOPLE GET.

35:05.125 --> 35:07.917
AND YOUR FATHER DID
ONE HELL OF A JOB,
DAWSON.

35:07.917 --> 35:11.875
HE MADE YOU INTO A MAN.

35:11.875 --> 35:14.250
AND HE MADE YOU
INTO A MAN THAT
PEOPLE CARE ABOUT

35:14.250 --> 35:16.083
AND ADMIRE AND RESPECT

35:16.083 --> 35:18.458
AND MOST IMPORTANTLY,
LOVE.

35:18.458 --> 35:22.041
SO, WHY AM I DOING THIS?

35:22.041 --> 35:23.708
I'M DOING THIS BECAUSE,
ONCE UPON A TIME,

35:23.708 --> 35:25.583
YOU AND I WERE
BEST FRIENDS.

35:25.583 --> 35:27.917
AND THAT MEANS THAT
WHENEVER YOU NEED ME,
I'M HERE.

35:27.917 --> 35:32.834
ANY TIME, ANYWHERE,
ANY PLACE. FOREVER.

35:34.125 --> 35:35.250
YOU UNDERSTAND THAT?

35:43.333 --> 35:44.375
WE SHOULD GET GOING.

35:55.166 --> 35:56.959
WHAT WAS HE LIKE?

35:56.959 --> 35:58.250
WELL, HE WAS A DAD.

35:58.250 --> 36:01.000
YOU KNOW, IN THE BEST
POSSIBLE WAY, I MEAN.

36:01.000 --> 36:04.792
HE WAS WARM AND CARING
AND JUST THE KIND
OF PAIN IN THE ASS

36:04.792 --> 36:06.208
YOU SECRETLY WANT
YOUR PARENTS TO BE.

36:08.542 --> 36:09.875
HOW'S DAWSON DOING?

36:12.417 --> 36:13.583
I WOULDN'T KNOW.

36:13.583 --> 36:15.291
DIDN'T WANT ANYTHING
TO DO WITH ME.

36:15.291 --> 36:18.083
I THOUGHT I'D BE ABLE
TO HELP HIM.

36:18.083 --> 36:19.917
I THOUGHT I WOULD BE
THIS INCREDIBLE RESOURCE

36:19.917 --> 36:22.041
'CAUSE I'VE BEEN THERE,
YOU KNOW?

36:22.041 --> 36:24.375
HE DIDN'T WANT ANYTHING
FROM ME.

36:24.375 --> 36:27.542
HE DIDN'T EVEN JUST
WANNA SIT THERE
IN SILENCE.

36:30.083 --> 36:32.458
HE WANTED ME
OUT OF HIS SIGHT.

36:33.750 --> 36:36.166
[CRYING]

37:21.875 --> 37:24.333
HONEY?
YEAH?

37:24.333 --> 37:28.333
WE'RE OUTTA MILK.
WOULD YOU MIND--

37:34.750 --> 37:37.375
[SOBBING]

38:12.417 --> 38:14.458
I CAN'T TELL YOU
HOW SORRY I AM
FOR YOUR LOSS, DAWSON.

38:14.458 --> 38:16.959
THANK YOU, MR. BRENNAN.
I APPRECIATE IT.

38:16.959 --> 38:19.667
HE WAS HERE, YOU KNOW.

38:19.667 --> 38:21.458
THAT NIGHT. YOUR FATHER.

38:21.458 --> 38:22.083
I KNOW.

38:22.083 --> 38:25.333
I ASKED HIM ABOUT YOU.

38:25.333 --> 38:28.959
HE SAID, UH, YOU WERE
A ROYAL PAIN IN THE ASS.

38:28.959 --> 38:31.792
[CHUCKLES]
THAT'S ME.

38:31.792 --> 38:34.208
HE WAS PROUD,
THOUGH.

38:34.208 --> 38:36.667
HOW DO I KNOW THAT, HUH?

38:36.667 --> 38:38.125
WELL, WHEN I MENTIONED
YOUR NAME,

38:38.125 --> 38:39.875
HIS WHOLE FACE
JUST LIT UP.

38:39.875 --> 38:42.166
HE SAID YOU WERE
THIS BRAVE KID,

38:42.166 --> 38:45.166
BUT HE HAD NO IDEA
HOW YOU GOT TO BE
THAT WAY.

38:45.166 --> 38:47.875
HE SAID YOU HAD
A ROMANTIC STREAK
A MILE LONG,

38:47.875 --> 38:50.834
AND HE SAID HE WAS PROUD
TO KNOW YOU.

38:50.834 --> 38:52.625
I'M SORRY IF THAT
MAKES YOU SAD, DAWSON,

38:52.625 --> 38:55.834
BUT I FIGURE
IF SOMEBODY
SAYS THAT ABOUT YOU,

38:55.834 --> 38:57.208
YOU OUGHT TO KNOW IT.

38:57.208 --> 38:58.500
OH, DON'T FORGET
YOUR CHANGE.

38:58.500 --> 39:01.500
AND BE CERTAIN
TO CONVEY MY CONDOLENCES
TO YOUR MOTHER,

39:01.500 --> 39:03.041
WOULD YOU?
THANK YOU. I WILL.

41:22.750 --> 41:25.625
ALL RIGHT! I THINK
I'VE GOT IT FIGURED OUT.

41:25.625 --> 41:27.750
OK, QUICK. LET'S GO,
EVERYBODY. GATHER.

41:27.750 --> 41:29.208
HURRY UP, 'CAUSE
WHAT THIS FAMILY
REALLY NEEDS

41:29.208 --> 41:30.250
IS ANOTHER PICTURE.

41:30.250 --> 41:32.208
OH, DON'T BE SO FRESH.

41:32.208 --> 41:33.291
YEAH. LOSE
THE 'TUDE, DUDE.

41:33.291 --> 41:35.083
CLEVER, DAD.
SMILES, PEOPLE.

41:43.458 --> 41:45.875
ALL RIGHT. GREAT!
THAT WAS WONDERFUL.

41:45.875 --> 41:47.291
I AM NOW LATE FOR THE MOVIES
WITH JOEY, JACK, AND JEN.

41:47.291 --> 41:48.000
HAVE FUN, HONEY.

41:48.000 --> 41:49.708
NO DRINKING
AND DRIVING.

41:49.708 --> 41:50.708
HEY, DAD,
JUST SO YOU KNOW,

41:50.708 --> 41:51.708
GOING TO THE MOVIES
IS NOT CODE

41:51.708 --> 41:52.834
FOR GOING OUT
AND GETTING WASTED.

41:52.834 --> 41:53.959
GO, GO, GO.
GET OUT OF HERE.

41:53.959 --> 41:56.000
HAVE FUN.
LATER, CREATORS.

41:56.000 --> 41:57.625
WELL,
THIS ONE'S HUNGRY.

41:57.625 --> 41:58.542
UH, NEED SOME HELP?

41:58.542 --> 42:02.333
NAH. STAY AND PLAY
WITH YOUR CAMERA.

42:02.333 --> 42:03.000
BOYS AND THEIR TOYS.

42:03.000 --> 42:04.959
[LAUGHS]

42:04.959 --> 42:07.625
COME ON.
